    "excerpt": "This is a live test of our new date-directory-based Markdown blog compilation system.",
    "tags": [],
    "contentHtml": "<p>Welcome to the new blogging system! This post is compiled dynamically from a raw markdown file stored in <code>/notebook/2026-06-26/post.md</code>.</p>\n<p>Here is a quick look at the features supported:</p>\n<h2>1. Bold and Italic Styling</h2>\n<p>You can write standard Markdown elements. For example, <strong>this is bold text</strong> and <em>this is italicized text</em>. You can also write <code>inline code</code> for technical terms.</p>\n<h2>2. Structured Lists</h2>\n<p>Here is a bulleted list:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Brutalist Grid Layout</strong>: Perfectly aligns with site dimensions.</li>\n<li><strong>Auto-compiling Script</strong>: Instantly compiles on <code>npm run dev</code> or <code>build</code>.</li>\n<li><strong>Easy Media Attachments</strong>: Place images in <code>attachments/</code> inside the date folder.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>And here is a numbered list of features:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Markdown Frontmatter Parsing (slug, title, date, excerpt, readTime).</li>\n<li>Word count automatic reading time estimation.</li>\n<li>Path rewriting of relative image URLs to match <code>/public</code> exports.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>3. Code Highlighting</h2>\n<p>Here is an example JavaScript code block:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"hljs language-javascript\"><span class=\"hljs-keyword\">const</span> compilePosts = <span class=\"hljs-built_in\">require</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\">&#x27;./scripts/compile-posts&#x27;</span>);\n\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\">// Compile notebook markdown files on dev server reload</span>\ncompilePosts.<span class=\"hljs-title function_\">watch</span>();\n</code></pre><h2>4. Blockquotes</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&quot;The details are not the details. They make the design.&quot;\n— Charles Eames</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Enjoy the new streamlined writing workflow!</p>\n"
